Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Computer Science Graduate* role with *Teradar*. I bring over three years of software engineering experience, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University, and I am excited to apply that background to internal tooling and automation work that supports fast-moving teams.

At Sperse and Qualitest, I have delivered the same core responsibilities outlined in this role. I built *web-based internal tools and dashboards* for non-technical teams, developed *data ingestion utilities* for *spreadsheets*, *CSVs*, and *exports*, and loaded transformed records into *structured databases* using *SQL* validation rules and practical *ETL concepts*. I also shipped *desktop or browser-based GUI tools* with *React* for *data cleaning*, *validation*, *mapping*, and *transformation*, and helped deliver *admin interfaces* for *browsing*, *searching*, and managing database content across large internal user bases (including systems supporting *30+ applications*). Across these environments, I consistently paired *automation scripts* with lightweight backend workflows and *export and reporting tools* so teams could remove repetitive manual work while keeping operations reliable.

My research and teaching experience complements that product engineering foundation. At Pace AI Lab, I built Python training and transformation pipelines for *StyleGAN* and *Stable Diffusion* on *CUDA* and *PyTorch*, then operationalized inference with *vLLM* and *Hugging Face* deployment workflows. I also led technical workshops for *+50* students on *CUDA*, *Mojo*, and agent frameworks, which strengthened my ability to communicate complex systems clearly to mixed technical audiences.

Teradar’s mission to save lives through terahertz vision, establish new benchmarks in automotive safety, and unlock the power of terahertz for the benefit of humanity strongly resonates with me. I would value the opportunity to contribute to that goal by building dependable internal software that helps your teams move faster with confidence. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

